[+] INTRODUCTION:

* ECB is an authentication mechanism in PHP based applications
* The entered message is splitted into blocks of X byte lengths
* Each block is encrypted seperately using a key
* Encryption Flow:
    >_ Plain text -> Block Cipher Encryption with a key -> Ciphered Output
* The ECB had the major secuurity implications
    >_ The ciphered blocks can be removed / moved without disturbing the encryption process


[+] VULNERABILITY:

* The cookie should be unique each time you login to an account
